@karpathy I call these "lessons" in my gptme agent template.

Agents write lesson files when they (or the user) figure out a workflow or way of solving a problem that it previously struggled with.

Relevant lessons are then pulled in via RAG when the context arises. Works really well!

@MasterTimBlais I think the most change come from: jacked -&gt; better self-image -&gt; smile more -&gt; people friendlier

i.e. not as a direct consequence of jacked.

I do think some people have been intimidated, when I notice I try to just smile and be overly nice, and that works to disarm.
